Alerts/Popups:
my_alert = driver.switch_to.alert()

my_alert.text() - gets text from the pop up
my_alert.accept()
my_alert.dismiss()


Authentication pop up:  add user name and pass word into the URL ofn the website

EX: "https://username:password@the-internet.herokuapp.com/basic_auth"

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

iFrames:

EX: https://testautomationpractice.blogspot.com/
EX: https://www.selenium.dev/selenium/docs/api/java/index.html?overview-summary.html

4 methods to switch to frame

switch_to.frame(name of the frame)
switch_to.frame(id of the frame)
switch_to.frame(web element)
switch_to.frame(index)

HTML names with form or frame or iframe, all represent a frame

Driver cannot switch from one iframe to the another directly in a web page.
We need to switch from page to frame and come back to page and then switch to the next frame.
******* driver.switch_to.default_content() ---- switches back to the main page.

INNER FRAMES:
Can be navigated using the web element and store it in a variable.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Handling Windows:

switch_to.window(Browser window ID - need to passed as a parameter)

Window ID's are dynamic, it will automatically be generated by the browser and changes everytime.
Windows ID's cannot be seen in HTML.

**** current_window_handle ----> It gives the window ID of the current window
******** window_handles -----> It gives the window ID of the multiple windows.


